&lt;p style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-style: italic;"&gt;It takes a special kind of diplomatic genius to pick a fight with the pope. Not a political rival. Not a foreign adversary. Not even a cable news host.

The pope.

And yet here we are, watching the Trump administration engage in a transatlantic war of words with Pope Leo XIV, a conflict that manages to be both geopolitically consequential and faintly ridiculous.&lt;/p&gt;
